@endnode

@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'Lightnix' where you want on
your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files or Libraries
are needed.

                             How to play?

  The game starts with 10 tiles of various shapes, randomly placed
on the board. To play, just click on one of these tiles. This will
generate 'lightning bolts' that will start from the clicked tile and
each lightning bolt will continue to move until it gets to the border
or another tile. If that tile is identical to the one from which the
lightning bolt started on, it will be eliminated. Note that the
clicked tile will remain intact.

  You get points according to the number of tiles that have been
eliminated by the 4 lightning bolts, as shown on the following table:

  1 tile  = 1 point
  2 tiles = 10 points
  3 tiles = 100 points
  4 tiles = 1000 points

  The game counts the consecutive number of times that lightning bolts
did not eliminate any tile, and add that number of tiles on the board
every time. Once a tile is eliminated, that number is resetted to zero.
Do not let the game board fill up completely (unless there is at least
two tiles of the same pattern), if that happens, the game will end.

@endnode

